1 1 New Section; Office of Professional Licensure and Certification; Expungement of Disciplinary
2 Action. AmendRSA310byinsertingaftersection10thefollowingnewsection:
3 310:10-a ExpungementofDisciplinaryAction.
4 I. Any current or past licensee of a board or the office who has been subject to disciplinary
5 action by the board that did not include revocation of license may file a petition with the office to
6 have it determine if the records from such action should be classified as confidential, not for public
7 release,andconsideredexpungedforreportingpurposesif:
8 (a) The application is submitted more than 3 years after the subject disciplinary action
9 occurred;
10 (b) Thedisciplinaryactiondidnotincludepermanentrevocationoflicense;
11 (c) The licensee has had no further disciplinary action against their license since the
12 disciplinaryactionidentifiedintheapplicationoccurred;
13 (d) Theofficehasnopendinginvestigationsagainstthelicensee;and
14 (e) Thelicensee'slicenseiscurrentlyingoodstanding.
15 II. Petitions that involve disciplinary action that only included a reprimand, administrative
16 fine, reasonable cost of investigation and prosecution, or a combination thereof shall be granted if
17 theymeettherequirementsinparagraphI.
18 III. AllotherpetitionsshallbegrantediftheymeettherequirementsinparagraphIandthe
19 petitioner also demonstrates that expungement will assist in the licensee's rehabilitation and is
20 consistentwithprotectingthepublicwelfare. Inmakingthisdetermination,theofficeshallconsider
21 the nature of the conduct that resulted in the disciplinary action; the nature of the disciplinary
22 action; and the current circumstances of the petitioner, including but not limited to their
23 rehabilitation, completion of the requirements of the disciplinary action, amount of time that has
24 passed since completion of the disciplinary action, testimonials, employment history, and
25 employmentaspirations.
26 IV. Any licensee who has their petition denied by the office shall have the right to a hearing
27 before the appropriate board or, if no such board exists, the office in accordance with RSA 310.
28 Requests for a hearing shall be made in writing to the appropriate board within 30 days of receipt of
29 theoriginalfinaldecision.
30 V. The executive director may adopt rules in accordance with RSA 541-A to implement this
31 section.

